    "reasoning": "First, analyze the problem: We need to build a finite state machine (FSM) for a Lemming character that walks either left or right, changes direction when bumped, and falls when ground is lost. The FSM needs to track the walking direction and handle state transitions based on inputs. Define three states: WALK_LEFT, WALK_RIGHT, and FALLING. Use areset as an asynchronous reset to set the initial state to WALK_LEFT. Define the state transitions according to the problem description. The FSM is a Moore machine because outputs depend only on the current state. We must handle all conditions properly: bump_left, bump_right, ground, and asynchronous reset. For state encoding, use localparam for clarity. Use always @(posedge clk, negedge areset) for the sequential logic. In the combinational block, define the next state based on current state and inputs. The output logic depends solely on the current state. Make sure outputs are assigned correctly and avoid using constructs like 'inside', 'unique', or explicit sensitivity lists in always blocks.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input areset,\n    input bump_left,\n    input bump_right,\n    input ground,\n    output walk_left,\n    output walk_right,\n    output aaah\n);\n\n    // Define states\n    localparam WALK_LEFT  = 2'b00;\n    localparam WALK_RIGHT = 2'b01;\n    localparam FALLING    = 2'b10;\n\n    // State register\n    logic [1:0] state, next_state;\n\n    // Sequential logic\n    always @(posedge clk, negedge areset) begin\n        if (~areset)\n            state <= WALK_LEFT;\n        else\n            state <= next_state;\n    end\n\n    // Combinational logic for next state\n    always @(*) begin\n        case (state)\n            WALK_LEFT: begin\n                if (!ground)\n                    next_state = FALLING;\n                else if (bump_left || bump_right)\n                    next_state = WALK_RIGHT;\n                else\n                    next_state = WALK_LEFT;\n            end\n\n            WALK_RIGHT: begin\n                if (!ground)\n                    next_state = FALLING;\n                else if (bump_left || bump_right)\n                    next_state = WALK_LEFT;\n                else\n                    next_state = WALK_RIGHT;\n            end\n\n            FALLING: begin\n                if (ground)\n                    next_state = (state == WALK_LEFT) ? WALK_LEFT : WALK_RIGHT;\n                else\n                    next_state = FALLING;\n            end\n\n            default: next_state = WALK_LEFT;\n        endcase\n    end\n\n    // Output logic (Moore machine)\n    always @(*) begin\n        walk_left = 1'b0;\n        walk_right = 1'b0;\n        aaah = 1'b0;\n\n        case (state)\n            WALK_LEFT: begin\n                walk_left = 1'b1;\n            end\n\n            WALK_RIGHT: begin\n                walk_right = 1'b1;\n            end\n\n            FALLING: begin\n                aaah = 1'b1;\n            end\n\n            default: ;\n        endcase\n    end\n\nendmodule"
}
